snippet: A state government attempt to create a high-speed rail line between Manhattan and Albany fell apart, leaving passenger cars rusting and spare parts collecting dust in a warehouse.
abstract: Four abandoned trains and a warehouse full of spare parts in Rotterdam, NY, are monuments to an ambitious plan to create a high-speed rail line between New York City and Albany; Gov Andrew M Cuomo administration, which has made a priority of consolidating government offices and selling surplus state property, will now try to sell the unused trains and their spare parts.
lead_paragraph: A state government attempt to create a high-speed rail line between Manhattan and Albany fell apart, leaving passenger cars rusting and spare parts collecting dust in a warehouse.

headline.seo: Cuomo Administration Looks to Sell 4 Trains From Failed Rail Project
headline.main: For Sale: 4 Weedy, Rusty Relics of a Doomed Rail Project
headline.print_headline: For Sale by the State: 4 Weedy, Rusty Relics of a Doomed Rail Project
